    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three spheres on three separate stands arranged in a row. From left to right, they are labeled Sphere 1, Sphere 2, and Sphere 3. Sphere 3 is connected by wire to ground. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"/images/af7ac1f83c5a2d939fa85897459dd64d.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, shown in the figure, are three identical conducting spheres that have been placed on top of insulating stands. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is connected to ground and is initially neutral, while spheres <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> each have an initial positive charge. The spheres are far enough apart that they do not affect the charge distributions on each other. A student brings the spheres into contact, two at a time, in the following order.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\"></p><ul class=\"unordered_list style:1\"><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span>